image.altText: An aerial view of a herd of buffalo walking through a small body of water, between long scrubby grass and trees.

props.synopsis: First Nations rangers and the CSIRO embark on a groundbreaking, space-based surveillance project to track and manage 1,000 wild bovine in remote northern Australia.

title.children: Indigenous rangers team up with scientists for project SpaceCows, the next frontier in feral pest control

image.altText: A close-up side profile of a teenage girl who bends forward in preparation for a sprint

props.synopsis: With a lack of resources in the regions, local aspiring athletes are faced with the prospect of having to leave their home towns to chase their dreams.

title.children: Addison dreams of competing in the Olympics. But she trains on a patch of grass that isn't flat

image.altText: A woman's silhouette in profile, as sunset, with the shadows of trees in the background.

props.synopsis: Late last year, a Darwin woman flew to the Gold Coast for a scan after being told she'd face a 10-week wait locally. Her doctor says it may have saved her breast.

title.children: Darwin woman forced to fly interstate for a cancer diagnosis, but the NT government denies there's a problem

image.altText: Blue and orange fabric badge on a blue shirt reads: Tasmania Police

props.synopsis: Bianca went to Hobart Police Station to report she'd been assaulted, assuming officers would protect her. Instead, they took out a family violence order against her — but perhaps she shouldn't have been so surprised.

title.children: Bianca's 'David and Goliath' battle with police is a cautionary tale for victims of family violence

image.altText: Clare O'Neil speaks at a press conference inside parliament house

props.synopsis: The federal government expects it will have to do more to overhaul Australia's immigration detention system after a High Court ruling prompted the release of 93 people, including murderers and sex offenders, from immigration detention.

title.children: Government facing the prospect of more people being released from immigration detention

image.altText: David McBride, wearing red glasses and looking off into the distance, outside the ACT court precinct.

props.synopsis: Most of the people we follow from the court run away from us. Not him. He stayed and chatted, happy to tell us he did it because he had felt he had to, writes court reporter Elizabeth Byrne.

title.children: A father and daughter school dance saw David McBride sneak home. That's when authorities swooped

image.altText: A crowd of people watch as a rocket launches out of a cloud of smoke

props.synopsis: About eight minutes into the test mission, a camera view tracking the Starship booster appears to show an explosion. The US Federal Aviation Administration will oversee an investigation.

title.children: 'We have lost the data': SpaceX's unmanned rocket explodes minutes after lift-off

image.altText: A white woman with greying brown hair standing in a kitchen with wooden cabinets

props.synopsis: Welfare recipients are often told to "just get a job". But health, economic and structural challenges mean it's not that simple.

title.children: Why 'just getting a job' isn't always so simple when you're on Centrelink payments

image.altText: A woman with shaved hair kisses a baby

props.synopsis: Casey McIntyre tells social media followers in a posthumous message she arranged to buy the medical debt of others as a way of celebrating her life.

title.children: 'I loved each and every one of you': Woman erases millions in medical debt after cancer death

image.altText: A high-up view of a housing estate, with mountain in background

props.synopsis: The boosted home buyers' grant will come into effect on Monday, and can also be used for granny flats or module homes.

title.children: Queensland first home owner grant doubles to $30k, can be used 'if your parents want to put a granny flat in the back'

image.altText: A boy smiling and wearing a beanie.

props.synopsis: SA Police has upgraded charges against a man in an alleged hit-and-run crash that killed Police Commissioner Grant Stevens's son at schoolies celebrations on Friday night, as his family, school and football clubs pay tribute to him.

title.children: 'Forever in our hearts': Tributes flow for Charlie Stevens as police upgrade charges against alleged hit-and-run driver

image.altText: Two dolls dressed in children's clothes are propped at desks while a doll in a teacher costume sits at a front desk.

props.synopsis: As the population of the Japanese village of Nagoro shrank, many buildings in the town were left abandoned. Tsukimi Ayano is one of the few residents left and has come up with a novel way to populate it — with dolls.

title.children: Would you move to a remote village for a 0 yen house? Here's what happened when Yasuyuki Fuke did

image.altText: A south asian man has an intense expression as he sings heavy metal, and a sensitive expression sings opera.

props.synopsis: While growing up in India, Shanul Sharma was teased by classmates for his high-pitched voice. After a brief stint in heavy metal, he's now using that voice to star in opera performances across the world.

title.children: Shanul used to sing in a heavy metal band. He's now dazzling audiences at the opera

image.altText: Scott Ledger holding a mango in a supermarket

props.synopsis: It takes two weeks for these Aussie mangoes to go from a farm to a US supermarket shelf. But for Manbulloo Mangoes it's been worth it.

title.children: $14 is what it costs in California to eat a juicy Australian mango

image.altText: People standing on top of large piles of rubble, destroyed buildings

props.synopsis: Most patients, doctors and displaced people have evacuated  Al-Shifa hospital, strikes on a refugee camp, a UN-run school, and residential blocks while Israel signals the expansion of their ground invasion.

title.children: Palestinians evacuate from Al-Shifa, as dozens die in strike on refugee camp

image.altText: Pacific Games

props.synopsis: Seven years in the making — and hundreds of millions of dollars later — this week Solomon Islands officially plays host to the 2023 Pacific Games, the region's "mini Olympics". But there's many other games going on.

title.children: It's the Pacific's 'mini Olympics' — some say it's more like 'a war zone'

image.altText: A scuba diver points a camera at coral under water.

props.synopsis: Underwater photographer David Hannan is on a mission to document the beauty of sea life. Along the way, he's had incredible encounters with some of the ocean's most playful, elusive and curious creatures.

title.children: 'Octopus quicker to train than a dog': The unique insights of an underwater photographer

image.altText: The spire of a catherdal in Wagga Wagga.

props.synopsis: The case brought by the victim of a notorious paedophile priest marked the first time a civil trial against the Catholic Church was heard by a jury, with a lawyer suggesting the high payout awarded served as a "warning shot" across the bow of institutions.

title.children: Record $3.3m church abuse payout could bring more survivors forward, lawyers say

image.altText: A silver F1 car, at night, on the Las Vegas Strip, driving for specators

props.synopsis: Max Verstappen has won the previous five races hosted in the United States, but Las Vegas provides a brand new test for the drivers.

title.children: Everything you need to know about the Formula 1 Las Vegas Grand Prix

image.altText: Eden Foster

props.synopsis: Labor's Eden Foster will take over the seat of Mulgrave from former Victorian premier Daniel Andrews following her by-election win. Premier Jacinta Allan says Labor anticipated a swing against it.

title.children: Swing against Labor in Mulgrave by-election was 'expected', Premier says after government retains seat

image.altText: A female artist performs at night, on stage, singing into a microphone, reaching out to a crowd

props.synopsis: A young Brazilian fan of US singer Taylor Swift died in Rio de Janeiro after falling ill inside the sweltering stadium where the superstar's concert was held, amid a record-breaking heat-wave across large swathes of Brazil.

title.children: Taylor Swift postpones second Rio concert after fan's death in Brazil heatwave

image.altText: Three different three-piece outfits of various colours laid out flat with two sets of bangles placed on them

props.synopsis: New outfits are a must on Diwali as it believed to attract blessings over the new year. An emblem of tradition and culture, we unpack some common ones and exhibit your best looks over this festive season.

title.children: Dazzling outfits often steal the limelight at any Diwali gathering. Here's your style glossary

image.altText: A close up for feral European honey bees.

props.synopsis: A good spring and plenty of food have increased the number of bees looking to establish new colonies, but as varroa mite moves through the region it could drastically reduce feral bee swarms.

title.children: Bee swarms on the rise as weather warms, but impact of varroa mite predicted to reduce swam frequency

image.altText: Sam Kerr smiles widely as she hugs her teammate Lauren James after a goal, as the crowd looks on.

props.synopsis: Sam Kerr is heavily involved with Chelsea's goals but doesn't find the target herself for once as Lauren James sinks Liverpool with a WSL hat-trick.

title.children: Sam Kerr turns provider in WSL as Lauren James steals Chelsea show against Liverpool

image.altText: Fire fighters work in an area destoryed by a drone attack.

props.synopsis: Russia carried out a major drone attack on Ukraine overnight, hitting infrastructure facilities and causing power outages in more than 400 towns and villages.

title.children: Power outages in more than 400 Ukrainian towns and villages after Russian drone attacks

image.altText: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma, wearing a cap and dark glasses, looks straight at the camera as he walks down steps.

props.synopsis: Rohit Sharma, India's captain, heaps praise on World Cup final opponents Australia ahead of the decider in Ahmedabad, dismissing the idea they're not a dominant side.

title.children: Indian skipper Rohit Sharma hails Australia pre-final as a 'complete side'

image.altText: Illegal fishers

props.synopsis: Commercial fishers operating in Australia's northern waters say illegal fishing activity is rampant, and they "don't bother" fishing in some areas due to the amount of catch being taken illegally.

title.children: Resurgence of illegal fishing 'unacceptable' as fishers say fish stocks are suffering

image.altText: A group of men and women in shallow women, handling a shark in water.

props.synopsis: Unlike on the Gold Coast, researchers say there is little knowledge of how many bull sharks are in the region's canals and waterways, which are often lined with multi-million dollar properties.

title.children: Anywhere between '20 or 20,000' bull sharks in Sunshine Coast waterways, as scientists attempt count
